    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="647"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6363 African Exploration and Development
                    Corp./9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-31T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 31, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. Your 418, August 31, noon.<note n="94" xml:id="d647fn94">Not printed.</note>
                    In reply to questions raised at the press conference this morning I stressed the
                    fact that we knew nothing about the African Exploration and Development
                    Corporation <pb facs="0882" n="780" xml:id="pg_780"/> or its plans and that we
                    had no advance information that the corporation was seeking a concession in
                    Ethiopia. I added that on the basis of facts now available I could not see that
                    any question presented itself to this Government.</p>
                <p>You should inform the Foreign Office in the above sense and keep the Department
                    fully and promptly informed of any developments that may come to the attention
                    of the British authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
